  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The dub step — not the genre, the physical act. ampAtk=0.001: instantaneous. ampRel=1.618 seconds (the golden ratio release, as all great dub engineers know). pressureAmt=0.6: the pressure compresses the attack into a click, and the release is the drop into silence. One note. One moment. The pressure holds.",
  "tags": ["bass", "submerged", "dub", "pressure drop", "attack", "golden ratio", "click", "percussive", "step"],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OCEANDEEP — The Abyssal Zone",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "ampAtk=0.001: the instantaneous onset. The note exists before the ear is ready.",
      "ampRel=1.618: Phi. The golden ratio. This is how dub engineers measure silence.",
      "The pressure drop is not a fall — it is a controlled descent into the waiting dark."
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "Play staccato for maximum effect — each note is a pressure event. The 1.618s golden ratio release means consecutive notes form a specific rhythmic relationship at most tempos. PRESSURE macro adds compression to the click-attack character. At full PRESSURE, the attack vanishes entirely.",
    "diagnosis": "ampAtk=0.001: instantaneous — the note is already there when you press the key. ampRel=1.618: golden ratio, a deliberate choice. pressureAmt=0.6: significant compression that shapes the attack transient into a deep click. filterCutoff=220: warm enough for the body of the note to feel physical. This is a rhythmic tool as much as a tonal one."
  },
